        <div class="section">
            <h2>What We Need From You</h2>
            
            <h3>Consistent Data Collection</h3>
            <p>This is the foundation. The minimum is 5 debriefs and 6 reflections to unlock your Journey Map, but the real value emerges with volume. Aim for:</p>
            <ul class="bullets">
                <li><strong>Post-ride debriefs after every ride</strong> (even the bad ones‚Äîespecially the bad ones)</li>
                <li><strong>One reflection per week</strong> (rotate through all 6 categories)</li>
                <li><strong>Honest, specific details</strong> over polished prose</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="margin-top: 15px;">The AI needs enough data points to distinguish between noise and signal. More data = more accurate pattern recognition = more useful insights.</p>

            <h3>Weekly Check-ins</h3>
            <p>Expect a brief survey or conversation each week about what's working, what's confusing, and what's frustrating. Your honest feedback matters more than positive feedback.</p>

            <h3>Technical Bug Reports</h3>
            <p>If something breaks, doesn't save, or behaves weirdly‚Äîtell us immediately. Include:</p>
            <ul class="bullets">
                <li>What you were doing when it happened</li>
                <li>What device/browser you're using</li>
                <li>Whether it's happened before</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Feature Requests & Ideas</h3>
            <p>If you think "it would be better if..." or "I wish it could..." ‚Äî that's exactly what we need to hear. No idea is too small or too weird.</p>

            <h3>Pattern Validation</h3>
            <p>When the AI identifies a pattern in your Journey Map or analysis, tell us if it rings true. Does the analysis match your lived experience? Where does it miss the mark? This feedback helps us refine the AI's pattern recognition.</p>

            <div class="emphasis">
                <strong>Remember:</strong> You're not just testing software‚Äîyou're helping us understand how riders actually think, reflect, and learn. Your participation shapes how this serves the entire dressage community.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Pilot Timeline & Milestones</h2>
            
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Week 1:</strong> Getting comfortable with the forms, building the debrief and reflection habit</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Week 2-3:</strong> First milestone reached‚ÄîJourney Map unlocked after 5 debriefs + 6 reflections (one per category)</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Week 3-5:</strong> Continue data collection, explore Journey Map, refine intentions and milestones</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Week 5-6:</strong> Additional AI coaching analysis unlocked (if sufficient data collected)</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Week 7-8:</strong> Pattern recognition deepens, assessment of overall progress tracking effectiveness</p>

            <div class="emphasis">
                <strong>Your Success Metric:</strong> By the end of 8 weeks, you should have 15-25+ debriefs and 8-12+ reflections. This volume allows the AI to identify genuine patterns, correlations you couldn't see, and provide actionable insights that feel specific to you rather than generic advice. The more data you collect, the more valuable the pilot becomes for your own riding development.
            </div>
        </div>

